result.execSummary:
Henri Tajaun Washington was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Henri Tajaun Washington was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Martin R. Tanz in court, defendant Henri Tajaun Washington not in court, in custody.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin  Defendant has been turned over to the State of Colorado.   Court grants State's motion and  orders case closed.

MCSD Extradition Unit contacted the court to advise that defendant would be picked up by Colorado authorities on 3/24/15.  Therefore, date is rescheduled to 3/25/15 at 8:30 a.m.  Parties notified by e-mail; copy in file.

Defendant Henri Tajaun Washington in court with attorney Martin R. Tanz.  Defendant Henri Tajaun Washington in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Colorado.  Defendant waived extradition hearing and consents to extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department and awaiting pick up by the State of Colorado.  Court orders case adjourned to make sure that the requesting state has picked up the defendant.  Court ordered case continued before Branch 20 for status to make sure that the requesting state picked up the defendant on the 3/23/15 date at 8:30 a.m.

Attorney Martin R. Tanz in court, defendant Henri Tajaun Washington not in court, in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense counsel waived his client's appearance.    Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.  Same bail.  Defense counsel requested a hearing date, as he indicated that his client is willing to waive extradition.  Court ordered case adjourned before Branch 20.  File retained in court.  Hearing scheduled for March 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Henri Tajaun Washington in court with attorney Martin R. Tanz.  Defendant Henri Tajaun Washington in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk:  bm
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Moroney, Branch 20.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Colorado.  Defendant contested extradition.  Arguments heard as to bail.  Court DENIES motion and ordered Defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for March 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
